        'At grade 5, ensure you can explain how Dickens uses language and structure to present key themes. Identify techniques (simile, metaphor, repetition) and explain their effects clearly. Show understanding of Dickens\'s purpose — he wanted to change attitudes towards the poor. Use relevant quotations from across the novella and explain what they reveal about characters and themes. Reference the five-stave structure and explain how Scrooge changes from beginning to end. Make sure you cover both the extract and the wider text, as WJEC requires both. Use topic sentences to organise your paragraphs and always return to the question to keep your argument focused.',
