      'WJEC Eduqas Paper 2 requires you to analyse an extract before discussing the wider novella. Spend the first half of your response on close, detailed analysis of the language and structure in the given extract. Use precise terminology and embed short quotations.',
      'Stevenson\'s novella is structured as a mystery — the truth about Jekyll and Hyde is withheld until the final two chapters. Discuss how this structure creates suspense and mirrors the theme of secrecy. The reader\'s experience of uncovering the truth parallels Utterson\'s investigation.',
      'Always consider multiple perspectives on Hyde. He can be read as a psychological symbol (the repressed id), an evolutionary regression (degeneration theory), a religious figure (Satanic evil), or a social commentary (the dark side of Victorian respectability). The strongest responses engage with several of these readings.',
      'Pay close attention to what is NOT said in the novella. Stevenson\'s technique of vagueness — Hyde\'s indescribable appearance, Jekyll\'s unspecified "pleasures" — is a deliberate narrative strategy. Analyse how this reticence creates horror and reflects Victorian culture\'s inability to speak openly about transgression.',
