      'For the highest grades, consider the novella\'s form. It is a "strange case" — a legal and medical term suggesting documentation and evidence. The narrative is assembled from multiple documents (Enfield\'s account, Lanyon\'s letter, Jekyll\'s statement), mimicking the process of building a case file. This formal choice reflects the themes of investigation, evidence, and hidden truth.',
