      'When analysing Hyde\'s violence, consider its escalation as a structural device. The trampling of the girl is disturbing but non-fatal; the murder of Carew is savage and deadly. This escalation mirrors Hyde\'s growing power over Jekyll and creates a mounting sense of dread that drives the narrative towards its catastrophic conclusion.',
      'For WJEC Eduqas, note that this text falls under "19th-century prose." Examiners expect you to show awareness of how the text reflects its historical period — the anxieties about science, evolution, moral degeneration, and the rigid social codes of late-Victorian Britain. Connect these contextual factors directly to your textual analysis rather than treating them as background information.'
